The paper deals with learning the structure of statistical relational frameworks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of first-order logical clauses and optimization methods also suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the focus on scalability and efficiency could also place the paper in the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
